text: This guide will walk you through setting up SalesBuddy AI for your sales team. First, connect SalesBuddy to your knowledge base by configuring the data integration settings. Next, invite team members and assign appropriate access roles. Then customize the AI responses to match your company's tone and terminology. Finally, train your team on effectively using the system with our interactive tutorials. The entire setup process typically takes less than a day.

text: The SalesBuddy API allows developers to integrate our conversational AI capabilities directly into their applications. All API requests must be authenticated using JWT tokens. To obtain a token, make a POST request to https://api.salesbuddy.ai/v1/auth/token with your API key in the header. The API has endpoints for conversation management, knowledge base updates, and analytics.

text: SalesBuddy AI employs enterprise-grade security with SOC 2 Type II compliance and GDPR readiness. All data is encrypted both at rest and in transit using AES-256 and TLS 1.3 protocols. Security penetration testing is conducted quarterly by independent security firms.

text: SalesBuddy AI can connect to multiple data sources to build its knowledge base. Supported sources include SharePoint, Google Drive, Confluence, internal wikis, product documentation, and custom databases. For each source, you can configure update frequency, access credentials, and content filters. The system will automatically extract, process, and index the content, making it searchable through the conversational interface. Advanced options include custom metadata mapping and incremental updating.

text: SalesBuddy AI integrates seamlessly with popular CRM platforms including Salesforce, HubSpot, and Microsoft Dynamics.
